      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(browser): My Browser node-anchored turn routing (stacks on #93411)",
        "body": "> **Stacked on #93411 — that must merge first.** This PR builds on the run-scoped `gateway.tools.byNode` primitive from #93411; its diff currently overlaps #93411's commits and will be rebased to the extension-only delta once #93411 lands. Draft until then.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Makes the \"My Browser\" extension actually *use* the node-anchored tool-scoping: routes the side-panel turn **through the hosting node** as an authenticated node-originated `agent.request`, so the gateway confines that turn's tools via `gateway.tools.byNode` (#93411), and pins the browser proxy back to that same node.\n- New wiring (on top of #93411's byNode core):\n  - **Node-host event emitter** (`node-event-emitter.ts`, re-exported via `plugin-sdk/gateway-runtime`): the node-host registers an emitter bound to its authenticated GatewayClient so node-host plugins can originate `node.event` `agent.request` over the node's own paired connection (cleared on disconnect).\n  - **Extension bridge** forwards a side-panel `agent.request` to that emitter via an `onAgentRequest` callback (threaded from `server-lifecycle`); acks acceptance, reply streams back over the side panel's own gateway subscription.\n  - **Side panel** (`sidepanel.js` / `background.js`) routes the turn through the node bridge, falling back to a direct gateway turn when no node hosts the bridge.\n  - **Browser tool** pins its node proxy to the turn's `hostingNodeId` (threaded through the plugin tool context), so a byNode-confined node turn drives the *same* node that hosts the user's tab — not an arbitrary connected browser node. Explicit `node=<id>` / `gateway.nodes.browser.node` keep override priority.\n- Out of scope: the `gateway.tools.byNode` primitive itself (#93411). The `driver:\"extension\"` browser mode may additionally need the upstream deprecation RFC resolved.\n\n## Linked context\n\nDepends on #93411 (gateway-core `byNode`). Related #93347 (closed — superseded by the authenticated-node approach).\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** routing a My Browser side-panel turn through the hosting node so `byNode` confines it, and pinning the browser proxy to that node.\n- **Real environment tested:** a real OpenClaw gateway + a device-paired node (loopback) on macOS, built from this branch; plus standalone bridge + browser-tool unit suites.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n  1. Gateway + paired node (loopback auto-approve), `gateway.tools.byNode[\"<node-id>\"] = { allow: [...] }`.\n  2. The node emits a node-originated `agent.request` over its authenticated connection.\n  3. Inspect the agent's resolved toolset; exercise the bridge `agent.request` routing and the browser-tool node selection under unit tests.\n- **Evidence after fix (copied live output):** byNode narrowing a real node turn — `[byNode] allow=[web_search,image] before=5{tts,web_search,web_fetch,image,canvas} after=2{web_search,image}` (run-scoped via threaded `hostingNodeId`). Bridge routing + browser-tool pin covered by tests below (75 passing in the browser + bridge suites).\n- **Observed result after fix:** the node-routed turn is byNode-confined; the bridge forwards `agent.request` to the node emitter and acks; the browser tool proxies to the turn's hosting node (and an explicit `node=` still overrides).\n- **What was not tested:** a single combined GUI Chrome recording of the side-panel→tab flow end to end (the extension→Chrome tab-driving half was proven + recorded in prior work; the new routing is proven via the box byNode run + the unit suites).\n- **Proof limitations or environment constraints:** gateway + node as two processes on one host (loopback pairing); the combined GUI recording is blocked by available disk (no VM image room).\n- **Before evidence:** without `byNode` for the node, the node-routed turn keeps all tools; without the hosting-node pin, the browser tool can auto-select a different connected browser node.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- `node-event-emitter` / bridge: `extension-bridge-server.agent-request.test.ts` — forwards `agent.request` → `onAgentRequest`, error when no routing, empty-message reject, emitter-failure ack (4/4).\n- Browser-tool hosting-node pin: `browser-tool.test.ts` — pins to the hosting node (resolves multi-node ambiguity), explicit `node=` overrides (browser suite 75 passing, no regressions).\n- `pnpm build` clean.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- **User-visible behavior change?** Yes — the side panel routes turns through the node when one hosts the bridge (with a direct-gateway fallback).\n- **Config/environment/migration change?** Uses #93411's `gateway.tools.byNode`; no new config here.\n- **Security/auth/tool-execution change?** Yes — turns become node-attributed (authenticated) so byNode can confine them; the browser proxy is pinned to the hosting node. Restriction-only via #93411.\n- **Highest-risk area:** node-origination + reply delivery. **Mitigation:** the bridge only acks; replies use the existing gateway subscription; fallback to a direct turn when no node is present.\n\n## Current review state\n\n- **Next action:** hold for #93411 to merge, then rebase this to the extension-only delta.\n- **Waiting on:** #93411 merge; the `driver:\"extension\"` mode RFC (if applicable); a combined GUI recording (disk-blocked).\n- **Addressed:** box-only proof hooks removed; node-routing + browser-pin wired and unit-tested.\n",
        "branch": "feat/my-browser-node-tools",
